  <para>
    When <xref linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Skeleton.New"/> is creating a new
    &skel; with triangular &elems;, it builds a rectangular array of
    quadrilaterals and divides each quad diagonally into two
    triangles.  The arrangement of the diagonals is determined by an
    <classname>Arrangement</classname> object.  <xref
      linkend="Figure-arrangement"/> illustrates the possibilities.
  </para>
  <figure id="Figure-arrangement">
    <title>Diagonal Arrangements for Triangular Skeletons</title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/conservative.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/conservative.eps"
	  format="EPS"/>
      </imageobject>
      <caption>
	<para>
	  The <userinput>conservative</userinput> arrangement, with
	  diagonals leaning to the right.
	</para>
      </caption>
    </mediaobject>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/liberal.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/liberal.eps"
	  format="EPS"/>
      </imageobject>
      <caption>
	<para>
	  The <userinput>liberal</userinput> arrangement, with
	  diagonals leaning to the left.
	</para>
      </caption>
    </mediaobject>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/moderate.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/moderate.eps"
	  format="EPS"/>
      </imageobject>
      <caption>
	<para>
	  The <userinput>moderate</userinput> arrangement, with
	  diagonals leaning to the right and to the left.
	</para>
      </caption>
    </mediaobject>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/middling.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/middling.eps"
	  format="EPS"/>
      </imageobject>
      <caption>
	<para>
	  The <userinput>middling</userinput> arrangement, with
	  diagonals leaning to the left and to the right.
	</para>
      </caption>
    </mediaobject>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/arrangements/anarchic.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
